{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013udHrU7mvaci5ppVodojVG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tasks complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## US-017 Summary\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **`fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/integrate.cu`** - Added anti-creep constants (`GRANULAR_V_THRESHOLD=0.01`, `GRANULAR_GAMMA_MIN=0.05`, `GRANULAR_RHO_FACTOR=0.95`) and two new kernel inputs (`sorted_density`, `sorted_shear_rate`). After the velocity magnitude clamp and before position update, GRANULAR particles with `|vel| < 0.01`, `rho > 0.95*rho0`, and `shear_rate < 0.05` get their velocity zeroed.\n\n2. **`fallingsand3d/integrate.py`** - Added optional `sorted_density` and `sorted_shear_rate` parameters (default to zero arrays for backward compatibility) and pass them to the kernel.\n\n3. **`fallingsand3d/simulation.py`** - Passes `sorted_density` and `sorted_shear_rate` from Step1 through to the integrate call.\n\n4. **`fallingsand3d/test_integrate.py`** - Added 6 new tests:\n   - `test_granular_anti_creep_settled` - settled particles get zeroed velocity\n   - `test_granular_anti_creep_flowing` - fast particles still flow\n   - `test_granular_anti_creep_low_density` - low density bypasses anti-creep\n   - `test_granular_anti_creep_high_shear` - high shear rate bypasses anti-creep\n   - `test_granular_no_jitter_5000_steps` - no jitter over 5000 steps\n   - `test_fluid_unaffected_by_anti_creep` - FLUID not affected\n\n**Test results:** 22/22 passed (16 existing + 6 new).\n\n<promise>COMPLETE</promise>"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":315,"cache_read_input_tokens":96612,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":315},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8366e700-f36a-49ec-85fd-f97c4934f324","uuid